  "id": "MAL-2026-10553",
  "summary": "Malicious code in home-mp-commons (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (552dd4c67a0d2119bf75c9949a6fd08f0e1734f485426af6ac22079c9240a2cb)\nhome-mp-commons@999.0.1 is a dependency-confusion squat (version 999.0.1, placeholder author/description). Its postinstall.js runs on npm install and issues an HTTPS request to a hardcoded Burp Collaborator subdomain jm93mcf6lwbl1ltezpqohn8t0k6bu4it.oastify.com, sending the installer's OS hostname (via require('os').hostname()) in the query string of /poc?evt=install\u0026pkg=home-mp-commons\u0026host=\u003chostname\u003e. The beacon fires automatically at install time and exfiltrates host identity to an attacker-controlled out-of-band domain regardless of a 'security research' self-label.\n",
